boostToMax().details: In the event that the new lock duration longer than the old, additional reward tokens are minted

canEject(address).details: there is an additional `ejectBuffer` that must have passed beyond the lockDuration before ejection is possible

constructor.details: prevent initializer from being called on implementation contract

depositByMonths(uint192,uint256,address).details: unless whitelisted, the receiver MUST be the caller and an EOA

params._amount: the number of tokens to deposit
params._months: the number of whole months to deposit for
params._receiver: address where reward tokens will be sent

depositByMonthsWithSignature(uint192,uin.details: params v,r,s are the ECDSA signature slices from signing the EIP-712 Permit message with the user's pk

params._deadline: the latest timestamp the signature is valid

eject(address[]).details: Other stakers are incentivised to do so to because it gives them a bigger share of the voting and reward weight.

params._lockAccounts: array of addresses corresponding to the lockId we want to eject

getAdmin().details: it's possible to have multiple admin roles, this just returns the first as a convenience.

getLock(address).details: accessing via the mapping returns a tuple. Struct is a bit easier to work with in some scenarios.

params._duration: in seconds of the timelock, will be converted to the nearest whole month

returns.multiplier: the %age (0 - 100%) of veToken per depositToken earned for a given duration

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

hasLock(address).details: depositByMonths should only be called if this returns false, else use increaseLock

params._amountNewTokens: the number of new deposit tokens to add to the user's lock

increaseAmountWithSignature(uint192,uint.details: params v,r,s are the ECDSA signature slices from signing the EIP-712 Permit message with the user's pk

params._deadline: the latest timestamp the signature is valid

increaseAmountsForMany(address[],uint192.details: receiver needs to have an existing lock

params._amountNewTokens: array of amounts to add to the receiver's lock with the same index
params.receivers: array or address to receive new tokens

initialize(address,address,uint32,uint32.details: deposit and veTokens are not checked for return values - make sure they return a boolean

returns._0: if current timestamp has passed the lock expiry date

migrate(address).details: the migrator contract must handle the reinstantiation of locks

previewDepositByMonths(uint192,uint256,a.details: will not work if the receiver already has a lock

params._receiver: the address to be credited with the depoist and receive reward tokens

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

setPRV(address).details: not checked for return values - ensure the token returns a boolean

params._user: address of the account to whitelist

terminateEarly().details: the PRV contract must be set to enable early termination. Underlying assets are transferred to this address.

COMPOUNDER_ROLE().notice: Compounder role can increment amounts for many accounts at once

PRV().notice: address of the Liquid Staking Derivative

boostToMax().notice: takes the user's existing lock and replaces it with a new lock for the maximum duration, starting now.

canEject(address).notice: checks if it's possible to exit a lock on behalf of another user

depositByMonths(uint192,uint256,address).notice: locks depositTokens into the contract on behalf of a receiver

depositByMonthsWithSignature(uint192,uin.notice: depositing requires prior approval of this contract to spend the user's depositToken         This method encodes the approval signature into the deposit call, allowing an offchain approval.

depositToken().notice: token locked in the contract in exchange for reward tokens

earlyExitFee().notice: Percentage penalty to be paid when early exiting the lock 10 ** 17; // 10%

eject(address[]).notice: Any user can remove another from staking by calling the eject function, after the eject buffer has passed.

ejectBuffer().notice: additional time period after lock has expired after which anyone can remove timelocked tokens on behalf of another user

emergencyUnlockTriggered().notice: callable by the admin to allow early release of locked tokens

getAdmin().notice: fetches the first DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE member who has control over admininstrative functions.

getLockMultiplier(uint32).notice: fetches the reward token multiplier for a timelock duration

hasLock(address).notice: checks if the passed account has an existing timelock

increaseAmount(uint192).notice: adds new tokens to an existing lock and restarts the lock. Duration is unchanged.

increaseAmountWithSignature(uint192,uint.notice: depositing requires prior approval of this contract to spend the user's depositToken         This method encodes the approval signature into the deposit call, allowing an offchain approval.

increaseAmountsForMany(address[],uint192.notice: adds new tokens to an array of existing locks from a spender address. Duration is unchanged.

increaseByMonths(uint256).notice: sets a new number of months to lock deposits for, up to the max lock duration.

isLockExpired(address).notice: overload to allow user to pass depositor address to check lock expiration

maxLockDuration().notice: maximum timetamp for tokens to be locked (i.e. block.timestamp + 36 months)

maxRatioArray(uint256).notice: incentivises longer lock times with higher rewards

migrate(address).notice: user can to transfer funds to a migrator contract once migration is enabled

migrationEnabled().notice: once enabled, users can call the `migrate` function

migrator().notice: the contract that will receive tokens during the migration

minLockAmount().notice: minimum quantity of deposit tokens that must be locked in the contract

minLockDuration().notice: minimum timestamp for tokens to be locked (i.e. block.timestamp + 6 months)

previewDepositByMonths(uint192,uint256,a.notice: allows a user to preview the amount of veTokens they will receive for a new deposit

setEjectBuffer(uint32).notice: sets the time allowed after a lock expires before anyone can exit a lock on behalf of a user

setMigrationEnabled(bool).notice: when set to 'true' by the owner, activates the migration process and allows early exit of locks

setMigrator(address).notice: sets the destination for deposit tokens when the `migrate` function is invoked

setMinLockAmount(uint192).notice: updates the minimum lock amount that can be locked

setPRV(address).notice: Sets address the Early termination will use

setPenalty(uint256).notice: Sets the percentage penalty to be paind when early exiting the lock 10 ** 17; // 10%

setWhitelisted(address,bool).notice: allows a contract address to receieve tokens OR allows depositing on behalf of another user

terminateEarly().notice: exits user's lock before expiration and mints PRV tokens in exchange, a termination fee may be applied.

triggerEmergencyUnlock().notice: if triggered, existing timelocks can be exited before the lockDuration has passed

veToken().notice: the token that will be returned to the user in exchange for depositToken

whitelisted(address).notice: whitelisted addresses can deposit on behalf of other accounts and be sent reward tokens if not EOAs

withdraw().notice: allows user to exit if their timelock has expired, transferring deposit tokens back to them and burning rewardTokens
